{
  "id": "RAW_24db2b",
  "title": "面向师生推出的 Gemini 教育工具套件",
  "url": "https://blog.google/outreach-initiatives/education/gemini-iste-2025/",
  "date": "2025-07-01 15:45:42",
  "author": "Akshay Kirtikar",
  "siteName": "The Keyword (blog.google) ",
  "content": "<html>\n <head></head>\n <body>\n  <uni-article-speakable style=\"height: 55px; margin-bottom: 36px; display: block;\" page-title=\"New Gemini tools for students and educators\" listen-to-article=\"Listen to article\" data-date-modified=\"2025-06-30T13:00:01.504611+00:00\" data-tracking-ids=\"G-HGNBTNCHCQ,G-6NKTLKV14N\" data-voice-list=\"en.ioh-pngnat:Cyan,en.usb-pngnat:Lime\" data-script-src=\"https://www.gstatic.com/readaloud/player/web/api/js/api.js\">\n   <!---->\n   <div id=\"uni-article-speakable\">\n    <!--?lit$798375131$--><span width=\"14px\">\n     <svg width=\"24px\" viewBox=\"0 0 66 66\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"uni-spinner uni-spinner--small\">\n      <circle class=\"loader-path\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"7\" cx=\"33\" cy=\"33\" r=\"25\"></circle>\n     </svg></span>\n   </div>\n  </uni-article-speakable> <!--article text-->\n  <div class=\"module--text module--text__article\" role=\"presentation\" data-analytics-module=\"{\n           &quot;module_name&quot;: &quot;Paragraph&quot;,\n           &quot;section_header&quot;: &quot;New Gemini tools for students and educators&quot;\n         }\">\n   <div class=\"uni-paragraph article-paragraph\" data-component=\"uni-article-paragraph\" data-compononent-initialized=\"true\">\n    <div class=\"rich-text\">\n     <p data-block-key=\"2lkiy\" class=\"drop-cap\">At this year’s International Society for Technology in Education (ISTE) conference, we announced new AI solutions designed to help every learner and educator. Here’s a closer look at what’s new.</p>\n    </div>\n   </div>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"module--text module--text__article\" role=\"presentation\" data-analytics-module=\"{\n           &quot;module_name&quot;: &quot;Paragraph&quot;,\n           &quot;section_header&quot;: &quot;New Gemini tools for students and educators&quot;\n         }\">\n   <div class=\"uni-paragraph article-paragraph\" data-component=\"uni-article-paragraph\" data-compononent-initialized=\"true\">\n    <div class=\"rich-text\">\n     <h2 data-block-key=\"2lkiy\">Introducing Gemini for Education</h2>\n     <p data-block-key=\"c51g\"><a href=\"http://edu.google.com/ai/gemini-for-education\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Gemini for Education</a> is a version of the <a href=\"http://gemini.google.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Gemini app</a> built for the unique needs of the educational community. Built with Gemini 2.5 Pro, <a href=\"https://blog.google/outreach-initiatives/education/google-gemini-learnlm-update/\">the world's leading model for learning</a>, Gemini for Education provides default access to our premium AI models, soon with significantly higher limits than what consumers get at no cost, plus enterprise-grade data protection and an admin-managed experience as a <a href=\"https://workspaceupdates.googleblog.com/2025/04/notebookLM-and-gemini-app-core-services-for-education-customers.html\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">core Workspace service</a> — all included in your Workspace for Education plan free of charge. This means educational institutions of all shapes and sizes can use cutting-edge AI with peace of mind that their data is protected by industry-leading security.</p>\n    </div>\n   </div>\n  </div><uni-image-full-width alignment=\"full\" alt-text=\"The image displays the title &quot;Gemini for Education&quot; in large, prominent text, accompanied by the descriptive subtitle, &quot;A version of the Gemini app built to meet the needs of the educational community.&quot; Surrounding the text are various icons, including a graduation cap, a pencil, a beaker, a globe, and a shield, symbolizing different aspects of education and learning. Below, an &quot;Ask Gemini&quot; search bar is visible, further emphasizing the app's interactive nature.\" external-image=\"\" or-mp4-video-title=\"\" or-mp4-video-url=\"\" section-header=\"New Gemini tools for students and educators\" custom-class=\"image-full-width--constrained-width uni-component-spacing\">\n   <!---->\n   <div class=\"image-full-width image-full-width--full image-full-width--constrained-width uni-component-spacing\" data-analytics-module=\"{&quot;module_name&quot;:&quot;Inline Images&quot;,&quot;section_header&quot;:&quot;New Gemini tools for students and educators&quot;}\">\n    <!--?lit$798375131$--><!--?lit$798375131$-->\n    <div class=\" image-full-width__media-asset \">\n     <!--?lit$798375131$-->\n     <div slot=\"image-slot\" style=\"display: block;\">\n      <img alt=\"The image displays the title &quot;Gemini for Education&quot; in large, prominent text, accompanied by the descriptive subtitle, &quot;A version of the Gemini app built to meet the needs of the educational community.&quot; Surrounding the text are various icons, including a graduation cap, a pencil, a beaker, a globe, and a shield, symbolizing different aspects of education and learning. Below, an &quot;Ask Gemini&quot; search bar is visible, further emphasizing the app's interactive nature.\" src=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Gemini_for_Education_announcement.width-100.format-webp_ywP14uq.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" data-loading=\"{\n            &quot;mobile&quot;: &quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Gemini_for_Education_announcement.width-500.format-webp_kWgmsfo.webp&quot;,\n            &quot;desktop&quot;: &quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Gemini_for_Education_announcemen.width-1000.format-webp_iHHPj32.webp&quot;\n          }\">\n     </div><!--?lit$798375131$--><!--?lit$798375131$--><!--?--> <!--?lit$798375131$--><!--?lit$798375131$--><!--?--> <!--?lit$798375131$--><!--?lit$798375131$--><!--?-->\n    </div><!--?--> <!--?lit$798375131$--><!--?lit$798375131$--><!--?-->\n   </div>\n  </uni-image-full-width>\n  <div class=\"module--text module--text__article\" role=\"presentation\" data-analytics-module=\"{\n           &quot;module_name&quot;: &quot;Paragraph&quot;,\n           &quot;section_header&quot;: &quot;New Gemini tools for students and educators&quot;\n         }\">\n   <div class=\"uni-paragraph article-paragraph\" data-component=\"uni-article-paragraph\" data-compononent-initialized=\"true\">\n    <div class=\"rich-text\">\n     <h2 data-block-key=\"2lkiy\">Expanding access to AI-powered tools for educators</h2>\n     <p data-block-key=\"bg0cf\">Today, we’re making Gemini in Classroom available to all Google Workspace for Education editions free of charge and <a href=\"https://blog.google/outreach-initiatives/education/classroom-ai-features\">launching more than 30 new capabilities</a> to help teachers plan and differentiate faster, like generating vocabulary lists with definitions and example sentences.</p>\n     <p data-block-key=\"7ohjq\">Additionally, since we launched <a href=\"https://services.google.com/fh/files/misc/gems_one_pager_education.pdf\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Gems</a> in the Gemini app, educators have been creating their own AI experts, like an “Interactive Simulations” Gem grounded on course assignments and readings to engage students. They’ve been requesting the ability to share their custom AI experts with others, and we’ll be launching this capability in the coming months.</p>\n     <p data-block-key=\"l5ib\">NotebookLM has become one of our fastest-growing apps in education, as educators and students 18+ turn to features like <a href=\"https://support.google.com/notebooklm/answer/16212820?hl=en\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Audio Overviews</a> to better understand their content and learn in new ways. In the coming weeks we’re rolling out Video Overviews, which let you turn your sources into <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-bjg2kqtrLc&amp;embeds_referring_euri=https%3A%2F%2Fblog.google%2F&amp;embeds_referring_origin=https%3A%2F%2Fblog.google\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">engaging educational videos</a> with the click of a button.</p>\n     <p data-block-key=\"6drm6\">We’re also expanding capabilities for educators with a paid <a href=\"https://edu.google.com/workspace-for-education/add-ons/gemini-education/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Google Workspace with Gemini</a> add-on. Whether it’s for professional development or announcing a new STEM program, educators can now create 8-second videos with sound effects using <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hNWfAznpp1o&amp;feature=youtu.be\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Veo 3 in Google Vids</a>. And rolling out now, <a href=\"https://support.google.com/docs/answer/16346789\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Gemini in Forms</a> can help create assessments and surveys faster than ever before. It can even generate a form based on a Doc, Slide deck or PDF from Drive and use Gemini to summarize form responses.</p>\n    </div>\n   </div>\n  </div><uni-image-carousel section-header=\"New Gemini tools for students and educators\" images=\"[\n    \n      {\n        \n          &quot;src&quot;: [&quot; https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/original_videos/ISTE2025_Workspace_Classroom_GeminiTab_Homepage_June_2025_16x9.mp4 &quot;],\n        \n        &quot;alt&quot;: &quot;A Google Classroom interface displaying \\u0022Google AI tools for educators\\u0022 with various options like \\u0022Outline a lesson plan,\\u0022 \\u0022Generate a quiz,\\u0022 and \\u0022Write a story.&quot;,\n        &quot;isVideo&quot;: true,\n        &quot;videoTitle&quot;: &quot;Gemini in Classroom&quot;\n      },\n    \n      {\n        \n          \n          \n          &quot;src&quot;: [&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Veo_3_in_Vids_PNG_1.max-1008x1008.format-webp.webp&quot;,&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Veo_3_in_Vids_PNG_1.max-1008x1008.format-webp.webp&quot;],\n        \n        &quot;alt&quot;: &quot;The image shows a video editing interface with a large preview of a university president speaking at a desk. Below is a video timeline with an audio waveform, indicating editing progress. On the right, a sidebar displays options to \\u0022Generate a video\\u0022 along with a text prompt that describes the president announcing a new STEM program.&quot;,\n        &quot;isVideo&quot;: false,\n        &quot;videoTitle&quot;: &quot;&quot;\n      },\n    \n      {\n        \n          &quot;src&quot;: [&quot; https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/original_videos/Gemini_in_Forms_1.mp4 &quot;],\n        \n        &quot;alt&quot;: &quot;A Google Forms interface shows \\u0022Hello, Erica, Let\\u0027s start creating.\\u0022 Users can select from suggested forms or input text, such as creating a physics quiz.&quot;,\n        &quot;isVideo&quot;: true,\n        &quot;videoTitle&quot;: &quot;Gemini in Forms&quot;\n      }\n    \n  ]\">\n   <!---->\n   <div class=\"article-module ga4-carousel\" data-component=\"uni-image-carousel\" data-analytics-module=\"{&quot;module_name&quot;:&quot;Article Carousel&quot;,&quot;section_header&quot;:&quot;New Gemini tools for students and educators&quot;}\" data-compononent-initialized=\"true\">\n    <div class=\"article-carousel\" aria-roledescription=\"carousel\">\n     <!--?lit$798375131$-->\n     <div class=\"article-carousel__slider\" aria-live=\"polite\" aria-atomic=\"false\" id=\"carousel-item-1751294147177\" data-slider-height-loaded=\"true\" style=\"height: 267.875px;\">\n      <!--?lit$798375131$--><!---->\n      <div class=\"article-carousel__slide article-carousel__slide--active\" role=\"tabpanel\" aria-roledescription=\"slide\" id=\"carousel-item-1751294147177-0\" aria-label=\"1 of 3\" style=\"left: 0%;\">\n       <figure>\n        <div class=\"article-carousel__image-wrapper\">\n         <!--?lit$798375131$-->\n         <div class=\"article-carousel__slide-img article-carousel__video-slide\">\n          <video autoplay=\"\" class=\"article-carousel__media\" loop=\"\" muted playsinline=\"\" type=\"video/mp4\" aria-label=\"A Google Classroom interface displaying &quot;Google AI tools for educators&quot; with various options like &quot;Outline a lesson plan,&quot; &quot;Generate a quiz,&quot; and &quot;Write a story.\" src=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/original_videos/ISTE2025_Workspace_Classroom_GeminiTab_Homepage_June_2025_16x9.mp4\">\n           Sorry, your browser doesn't support embedded videos, but don't worry, you can <a href=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/original_videos/ISTE2025_Workspace_Classroom_GeminiTab_Homepage_June_2025_16x9.mp4\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">download it</a>and watch it with your favorite video player!\n          </video>\n         </div>\n        </div><!--?lit$798375131$-->\n        <figcaption class=\"article-carousel__caption\">\n         <!--?lit$798375131$-->\n        </figcaption>\n       </figure>\n      </div><!----><!----><!----><!----><!---->\n     </div><!--?lit$798375131$-->\n     <div class=\"article-carousel__navigation ga4-bullets\" role=\"tablist\">\n      <!--?lit$798375131$--><!---->\n      <button class=\"article-carousel__navigation-button article-carousel__navigation-button--active\" type=\"button\" role=\"tab\" aria-selected=\"true\" aria-controls=\"carousel-item-1751294147177-0\" data-index=\"1\"><!--?lit$798375131$-->Jump to position 1</button><!----><!---->\n      <button class=\"article-carousel__navigation-button\" type=\"button\" role=\"tab\" aria-selected=\"false\" aria-controls=\"carousel-item-1751294147177-1\" data-index=\"2\"><!--?lit$798375131$-->Jump to position 2</button><!----><!---->\n      <button class=\"article-carousel__navigation-button\" type=\"button\" role=\"tab\" aria-selected=\"false\" aria-controls=\"carousel-item-1751294147177-2\" data-index=\"3\"><!--?lit$798375131$-->Jump to position 3</button><!---->\n     </div>\n    </div>\n   </div>\n  </uni-image-carousel>\n  <div class=\"module--text module--text__article\" role=\"presentation\" data-analytics-module=\"{\n           &quot;module_name&quot;: &quot;Paragraph&quot;,\n           &quot;section_header&quot;: &quot;New Gemini tools for students and educators&quot;\n         }\">\n   <div class=\"uni-paragraph article-paragraph\" data-component=\"uni-article-paragraph\" data-compononent-initialized=\"true\">\n    <div class=\"rich-text\">\n     <h2 data-block-key=\"hnphk\">Helping students learn confidently</h2>\n     <p data-block-key=\"fke3n\">Students 18+ can now generate personalized quizzes for any subject using Gemini Canvas, so they can prepare for exams and test their understanding. This will be expanding to students under 18 in the coming weeks. Gemini will also soon provide visuals, like interactive diagrams, in its responses to help learners understand complex concepts more easily.</p>\n     <p data-block-key=\"bebka\">We’re also announcing teacher-led AI experiences for students, reflecting our continued efforts to provide more <a href=\"https://blog.google/outreach-initiatives/education/workspace-gemini-classroom-iste-2024/\">safe, responsible AI tools</a> that also give students agency to learn in the ways that work best for them. In the coming months educators will be able to assign Gems and notebooks from NotebookLM grounded in their class materials directly to students in Google Classroom. We’re updating Gemini LTI so educators can also do this in PowerSchool Schoology Learning and Canvas by Instructure.</p>\n    </div>\n   </div>\n  </div><uni-image-carousel section-header=\"New Gemini tools for students and educators\" images=\"[\n    \n      {\n        \n          &quot;src&quot;: [&quot; https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/original_videos/gemini-quizzes_tc3POnO.mp4 &quot;],\n        \n        &quot;alt&quot;: &quot;A phone screen displays the time, date (Tuesday, May 20), temperature (68°F), and \\u0022Google I/O 2025.\\u0022 A notification from Gemini states, \\u0022You have a physics exam coming up. Let\\u0027s test your knowledge on thermodynamics. Ready to review?\\u0022 with options for \\u0022Live Chat\\u0022 and \\u0022Practice Quiz.\\u0022&quot;,\n        &quot;isVideo&quot;: true,\n        &quot;videoTitle&quot;: &quot;Gemini quiz&quot;\n      },\n    \n      {\n        \n          &quot;src&quot;: [&quot; https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/original_videos/Visual_learning_in_Gemini_2.mp4 &quot;],\n        \n        &quot;alt&quot;: &quot;A Gemini interface with a text box at the top saying, \\u0022Give me an overview of animal cell biology.\\u0022 Below it, a detailed explanation of animal cells is provided, along with a \\u0022View diagram\\u0022 button overlaying an image of an animal cell.&quot;,\n        &quot;isVideo&quot;: true,\n        &quot;videoTitle&quot;: &quot;visual learning&quot;\n      },\n    \n      {\n        \n          &quot;src&quot;: [&quot; https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/original_videos/ISTE2025_Gemini_LTI_June_2025_16x9.mp4 &quot;],\n        \n        &quot;alt&quot;: &quot;: The Gemini interface shows a \\u0022Manage notebooks\\u0022 section with options to \\u0022Create new\\u0022 or \\u0022Add to course.\\u0022 A list of existing notebooks is visible.&quot;,\n        &quot;isVideo&quot;: true,\n        &quot;videoTitle&quot;: &quot;Gemini LTI M2&quot;\n      }\n    \n  ]\">\n   <!---->\n   <div class=\"article-module ga4-carousel\" data-component=\"uni-image-carousel\" data-analytics-module=\"{&quot;module_name&quot;:&quot;Article Carousel&quot;,&quot;section_header&quot;:&quot;New Gemini tools for students and educators&quot;}\" data-compononent-initialized=\"true\">\n    <div class=\"article-carousel\" aria-roledescription=\"carousel\">\n     <!--?lit$798375131$-->\n     <div class=\"article-carousel__slider\" aria-live=\"polite\" aria-atomic=\"false\" id=\"carousel-item-1751294147178\" data-slider-height-loaded=\"true\" style=\"height: 267.875px;\">\n      <!--?lit$798375131$--><!---->\n      <div class=\"article-carousel__slide article-carousel__slide--active\" role=\"tabpanel\" aria-roledescription=\"slide\" id=\"carousel-item-1751294147178-0\" aria-label=\"1 of 3\" style=\"left: 0%;\">\n       <figure>\n        <div class=\"article-carousel__image-wrapper\">\n         <!--?lit$798375131$-->\n         <div class=\"article-carousel__slide-img article-carousel__video-slide\">\n          <video autoplay=\"\" class=\"article-carousel__media\" loop=\"\" muted playsinline=\"\" type=\"video/mp4\" aria-label=\"A phone screen displays the time, date (Tuesday, May 20), temperature (68°F), and &quot;Google I/O 2025.&quot; A notification from Gemini states, &quot;You have a physics exam coming up. Let's test your knowledge on thermodynamics. Ready to review?&quot; with options for &quot;Live Chat&quot; and &quot;Practice Quiz.&quot;\" src=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/original_videos/gemini-quizzes_tc3POnO.mp4\">\n           Sorry, your browser doesn't support embedded videos, but don't worry, you can <a href=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/original_videos/gemini-quizzes_tc3POnO.mp4\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">download it</a>and watch it with your favorite video player!\n          </video>\n         </div>\n        </div><!--?lit$798375131$-->\n        <figcaption class=\"article-carousel__caption\">\n         <!--?lit$798375131$-->\n        </figcaption>\n       </figure>\n      </div><!----><!----><!----><!----><!---->\n     </div><!--?lit$798375131$-->\n     <div class=\"article-carousel__navigation ga4-bullets\" role=\"tablist\">\n      <!--?lit$798375131$--><!---->\n      <button class=\"article-carousel__navigation-button article-carousel__navigation-button--active\" type=\"button\" role=\"tab\" aria-selected=\"true\" aria-controls=\"carousel-item-1751294147178-0\" data-index=\"1\"><!--?lit$798375131$-->Jump to position 1</button><!----><!---->\n      <button class=\"article-carousel__navigation-button\" type=\"button\" role=\"tab\" aria-selected=\"false\" aria-controls=\"carousel-item-1751294147178-1\" data-index=\"2\"><!--?lit$798375131$-->Jump to position 2</button><!----><!---->\n      <button class=\"article-carousel__navigation-button\" type=\"button\" role=\"tab\" aria-selected=\"false\" aria-controls=\"carousel-item-1751294147178-2\" data-index=\"3\"><!--?lit$798375131$-->Jump to position 3</button><!---->\n     </div>\n    </div>\n   </div>\n  </uni-image-carousel>\n  <div class=\"module--text module--text__article\" role=\"presentation\" data-analytics-module=\"{\n           &quot;module_name&quot;: &quot;Paragraph&quot;,\n           &quot;section_header&quot;: &quot;New Gemini tools for students and educators&quot;\n         }\">\n   <div class=\"uni-paragraph article-paragraph\" data-component=\"uni-article-paragraph\" data-compononent-initialized=\"true\">\n    <div class=\"rich-text\">\n     <h2 data-block-key=\"uvjog\">Approaching AI in education responsibly</h2>\n     <p data-block-key=\"e6d8q\">Earlier this year we <a href=\"https://blog.google/outreach-initiatives/education/ai-literacy-day-2025/\">announced</a> we would be bringing Gemini to younger users with supervision tools and controls for parents and educators. We’ve consulted with child safety and development experts to help shape our content policies, partnered with learning science experts, tested with youth advisory panels and added <a href=\"https://workspaceupdates.googleblog.com/2025/04/notebookLM-and-gemini-app-core-services-for-education-customers.html\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">extra data protection</a> for all education users, meaning Google will not use data from chats to improve AI models. The Gemini app is now available to students of all ages and as a <a href=\"https://workspaceupdates.googleblog.com/2025/04/notebookLM-and-gemini-app-core-services-for-education-customers.html\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">core Workspace service</a>, and in the coming months we’re making <a href=\"http://notebooklm.google.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">NotebookLM</a> available to students of all ages while using their Google Workspace for Education accounts to help them study and better understand their class materials.</p>\n     <p data-block-key=\"3sdan\">Gemini has stricter content policies that help prevent potentially inappropriate or harmful responses for users under 18, as will NotebookLM when it becomes available to users under 18. Gemini includes a <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vazwd0HOohE\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">youth onboarding experience</a> with AI literacy resources — endorsed by ConnectSafely and Family Online Safety Institute — and the first time a user asks a fact-based question, Gemini <a href=\"https://support.google.com/gemini/answer/14143489?hl=en&amp;co=GENIE.Platform%3DAndroid\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">double-checks</a> using Google Search to find content on the web that’s likely similar to or likely different to its responses<b>.</b> Educators can further teach AI literacy with this <a href=\"https://services.google.com/fh/files/misc/be_internet_awesome_ai_literacy_guide.pdf\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">guide</a> and <a href=\"https://services.google.com/fh/files/misc/google_teaching_responsible_ai.pdf\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">lesson plan</a>, and learn more themselves with no-cost courses designed for both <a href=\"https://skillshop.exceedlms.com/student/path/1178011-get-started-with-google-ai-in-k12-education\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">K-12</a> and <a href=\"https://skillshop.exceedlms.com/student/path/1470990-get-started-with-google-ai-in-higher-education\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">higher education</a>.</p>\n     <p data-block-key=\"dkm4a\">To ensure schools are always in control, admins can manage who has access to the <a href=\"https://support.google.com/a/answer/14571493?hl=en&amp;co=DASHER._Family%3DEducation&amp;oco=0#gemini-setting\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Gemini app</a> and <a href=\"https://support.google.com/a/answer/15239506?hl=en_fm&amp;ref_topic=15995054\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">NotebookLM</a> in the Admin console, search Gemini app conversations in their domain using Vault, and view usage reporting. And with Gemini in Google Workspace for Education recently being awarded the <a href=\"https://privacy.commonsense.org/evaluation/Gemini-in-Google-Workspace-for-Education\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Common Sense Media Privacy Seal</a>, admins can be confident their users’ data is protected when using Gemini.</p>\n    </div>\n   </div>\n  </div><uni-image-full-width alignment=\"full\" alt-text=\"Gemini logo alongside the Common Sense Privacy Verified seal.\" external-image=\"\" or-mp4-video-title=\"\" or-mp4-video-url=\"\" section-header=\"New Gemini tools for students and educators\" custom-class=\"image-full-width--constrained-width uni-component-spacing\">\n   <!---->\n   <div class=\"image-full-width image-full-width--full image-full-width--constrained-width uni-component-spacing\" data-analytics-module=\"{&quot;module_name&quot;:&quot;Inline Images&quot;,&quot;section_header&quot;:&quot;New Gemini tools for students and educators&quot;}\">\n    <!--?lit$798375131$--><!--?lit$798375131$-->\n    <div class=\" image-full-width__media-asset \">\n     <!--?lit$798375131$-->\n     <div slot=\"image-slot\" style=\"display: block;\">\n      <img alt=\"Gemini logo alongside the Common Sense Privacy Verified seal.\" src=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/026-ISTE-EDU-Gemini__Common_Sense.width-100.format-webp.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" data-loading=\"{\n            &quot;mobile&quot;: &quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/026-ISTE-EDU-Gemini__Common_Sense.width-500.format-webp.webp&quot;,\n            &quot;desktop&quot;: &quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/026-ISTE-EDU-Gemini__Common_Sens.width-1000.format-webp.webp&quot;\n          }\">\n     </div><!--?lit$798375131$--><!--?lit$798375131$--><!--?--> <!--?lit$798375131$--><!--?lit$798375131$--><!--?--> <!--?lit$798375131$--><!--?lit$798375131$--><!--?-->\n    </div><!--?--> <!--?lit$798375131$--><!--?lit$798375131$--><!--?-->\n   </div>\n  </uni-image-full-width>\n  <div class=\"module--text module--text__article\" role=\"presentation\" data-analytics-module=\"{\n           &quot;module_name&quot;: &quot;Paragraph&quot;,\n           &quot;section_header&quot;: &quot;New Gemini tools for students and educators&quot;\n         }\">\n   <div class=\"uni-paragraph article-paragraph\" data-component=\"uni-article-paragraph\" data-compononent-initialized=\"true\">\n    <div class=\"rich-text\">\n     <p data-block-key=\"wmjhm\">Learn more about everything we’re announcing in our <a href=\"http://goo.gle/gfe-launch-guide-iste25\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">launch guide</a>, and <a href=\"https://edu.google.com/intl/ALL_us/communications/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">sign up for updates</a> from Google for Education as these features roll out.<span class=\"tombstone\"></span></p>\n    </div>\n   </div>\n  </div>\n </body>\n</html>",
  "aiSummary": "谷歌发布教育版 Gemini，为师生提供 30 余款全新 AI 工具，包含强化学习功能、个性化随堂测验，并通过常识媒体隐私认证实现完善的青少年保护机制。",
  "oneSentenceSummary": "谷歌发布教育版 Gemini，为师生提供 30 余款全新 AI 工具，包含强化学习功能、个性化随堂测验，并通过常识媒体隐私认证实现完善的青少年保护机制。",
  "summary": "谷歌在 2025 年国际教育技术协会(ISTE)大会上正式推出教育版 Gemini（人工智能教学平台），该专用版本为学校提供具备企业级数据保护的高级 AI 模型。此次发布包含 30 多项教学工具创新，包括智能词汇表生成、NotebookLM（智能笔记应用）的视频摘要功能，以及 Gemini 与 Google 表单的深度整合。学生端新增通过 Gemini Canvas（智能学习画布）生成个性化随堂测验，以及可视化复杂概念的互动图表功能。谷歌特别强调负责任的 AI 应用，实施严格的青少年内容审查机制，为 18 岁以下用户定制 AI 素养入门课程，并提供完善的管理控制功能。该平台近期斩获常识媒体隐私认证，其教育数据保护标准已获权威验证。",
